/.lake

# Jekyll homepage artifacts (when previewing locally).
home_page/_site
home_page/.bundle
home_page/.jekyll-cache
home_page/.jekyll-metadata
home_page/Gemfile.lock
home_page/vendor

# Generated by leanprover-community/upstreaming-dashboard-action during CI.
home_page/_includes/_upstreaming_dashboard/

# Blueprint artifacts (TeX build is gitignored separately under blueprint/.gitignore).
blueprint/print/
blueprint/web/

# Local-only reference PDFs (papers pulled for citation verification).
.refs/

# Personal Claude Code harness setup — but ship the project slash
# commands under .claude/commands/, the coordinator subagent
# definitions under .claude/agents/, the safety hooks under
# .claude/hooks/, and the project settings.json that wires the hooks:
# they carry workflow lessons and mechanical guards that should
# survive a fresh clone. (A bare `.claude/` ignore kept
# coordinate-phase.md and the lake-update guard machine-local; the
# guard's motivating OOM crash is enharmonic 2026-06-10. The `.claude/*`
# re-exclude silently dropped .claude/agents/ until the leading
# `!.claude/agents/` was added — template sync 2026-07-09.) Personal
# overrides go in settings.local.json, which stays ignored. The
# leading `!.claude/` also overrides any user-global `**/.claude`
# exclude.
!.claude/
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/settings.json
